Carlsson, Gustaf Adolf, vicar, Mariestad, born on 6/11/1890 in Alingsås to estate owner Olaus C. and Augusta Carlsson. Married on 26 to Ingeborg Andersson. Children: Britta born in 1929. Education: graduated from Skara in 1911, Bachelor of Arts in 1921, Bachelor of Theology and ordained in Skara Diocese in 1923. Vicar in Fägre in 1923, curate in Korsberga in 1924, parish priest in Sventorp in 1928, curate in Mariestad since 1934, cathedral notary since the same year, appointed as a vicar in 1935.

Carlsson, Gustaf Börje, vicar, Hok, born on 5/4/1907 in Sunnersberg, Skaraborg County, to Emil C. and Anna Gustafsdotter. Married on 34 to Ruby Sölvén. Children: Anders born in 1937, Peter in 1943. Education: Graduated from Jönköping in 1927, studied theology and received a Bachelor of Philosophy from Lund in 1929, Bachelor of Theology and passed practical theological examination in 1933, ordained in Växjö Diocese in 1934. Has served as an assistant minister in Fryele, deputy vicar in Öskarshamn, and vice pastor in Björkö, Tolg, and Barkeryd. Vicar in Svenarum in 1938 and has served there since 1942.

Carlsson, Johan Gustaf, high school teacher, Gothenburg, born on 7/7/1884 in Växjö to Carl Arvidsson and Märta Pettersdotter. Married on 12 to Signe Holm. Children: Per Sköldenberg, born in 1913, civil engineer, Bengt Sköldenberg, born in 1918, Bachelor of Arts, journalist. Education: Master's degree in Växjö in 1903, Bachelor of Arts from Lund in 1908, probationary year in 1912. Traveled to Germany in 1908, 1923, 1927, and 1929, Austria in 1923, Belgium and France in 1934. Visitors at the Kristineberg Zoological Station in 1905, scholar and assistant at the zoological institute in Lund from 1906 to 1909, temporary teacher in Kalmar in 1909, teacher in Eslöv from 1909 to 1910, temporary lecturer in Kalmar from 1910 to 1911, assistant in Karlshamn in 1912, in Ystad in 1918, adjutant in geography and biology with a health science specialty at Hvitfeldtska high school in Gothenburg since 1931. Member of the First Chamber of the Parliament from 1920 to 1923, holding various positions in Ystad, including member of the city council, chairman of the city audit committee, review officer for the county hospital, and deputy chairman of the monastery board, as well as member of the board for antiquities. Speaker for the Population Bureau for Popular Science Seminars in Gothenburg since 1938. Works: scientific dissertations and essays in popular scientific journals, reviews.
